org.soulwing.cdi.properties.spi

Interface Optional

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    InternetAddressPropertyConverter, OptionalPropertyConverter, ScheduleExpressionPropertyConverter

    public interface Optional
    A provider component that depends on classes or other resources that might not be available at runtime can implement this interface to indicate that it is optional.
    Author:
    Carl Harris

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isAvailable()
      Tests whether this provider is available.

    • Method Detail

      • isAvailable

        boolean isAvailable()
        Tests whether this provider is available.

        This method will be invoked once after the component is instantiated via its constructor. If the return value is false no subsequent method invocations will occur on the provider instance.

        Returns:
        true if the provider is should be considered available
